.TH "wb_wait_for_completion" 9 "wb_wait_for_completion" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wb_wait_for_completion \- wait for completion of bdi_writeback_works
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" wb_wait_for_completion
.BI "(struct wb_completion *done "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "done" 12
target wb_completion
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for one or more work items issued to \fIbdi\fP with their ->done field
set to \fIdone\fP, which should have been initialized with
\fBDEFINE_WB_COMPLETION\fP.  This function returns after all such work items
are completed.  Work items which are waited upon aren't freed
automatically on completion.
